You are helping implement features for a simple browser/text-based game with a virtual bank system.

Current bank already has:

- User accounts with a "coins" balance (integer)
- Ability to buy coins via Stripe (already implemented)
- Basic methods like: add_coins(user_id, amount), subtract_coins(user_id, amount), get_balance(user_id)

Now implement a collateral-based loan system with these exact rules:

1. Allowed collateral amounts (exact only): 5000, 10000, 20000 coins
2. Loan amount = exactly 60% of collateral (integer division, no rounding up)
   → 5000 collateral → 3000 loan
   → 10000 collateral → 6000 loan
   → 20000 collateral → 12000 loan
3. No interest, no fees, no time limit
4. A user can have at most ONE active loan at a time
5. When taking a loan:
   - Check user has enough coins
   - Check requested collateral is one of the three allowed values
   - Lock/remove the collateral coins from user's available balance
   - Add the loan amount (60%) to user's available balance
   - Record the loan: collateral_amount, borrowed_amount, user_id, timestamp
6. When repaying:
   - User must repay EXACTLY the borrowed amount
   - If repayment == borrowed_amount → return the FULL original collateral to user's balance
   - Clear the active loan record
   - If repayment < borrowed → error (partial payments not allowed)
   - If repayment > borrowed → error (overpayment not allowed)
7. Error cases to handle and return clear messages for:
   - Insufficient balance for collateral
   - Invalid collateral amount (not 5k/10k/20k)
   - User already has an active loan
   - Trying to repay wrong amount
   - No active loan when trying to repay
   - Trying to take loan with 0 coins etc.

Please provide:
• Suggested new database fields / schema additions (simple key-value or document style is fine)
• New methods you would add to the Bank class/service, for example:

- request_loan(user_id, collateral_amount)
- repay_loan(user_id, repayment_amount)
- get_active_loan(user_id) // to show status
  • Clear pseudocode or real Python code (whichever is clearer) showing the logic inside those methods
  • Example usage / flow for both taking and repaying a loan

Keep the implementation as simple and safe as possible — no interest, no automatic liquidation, no complex math.
